description.plain:
Joseph Mount on working with Biig Piig, NME.

“The song clicked with this feeling she’d had lately and the atmosphere of the track really worked with that. That kind of skill is a really rare thing to happen; we weren’t in the same physical space when we wrote the song and it touched something in there. I was genuinely blown away by what she’d done.

“It’s a sentiment in a song that I haven’t heard before, or heard articulated in such a nice way. The project was already going well and it was interesting and I got back from Jess and I thought it was just so brilliant; I never imagined it would be so good.”

body.plain: “Shh” has a melancholic tone, it seems to be talking about a past lover or really close friend that protected her and supported her when she was going through a dark time.

annotations:
Es gracias a ti
 Ya no tengo miedo
 Nunca de mis sueños
 Ni de mi infierno

“Thanks to you
I am not afraid anymore
Not of my dreams
Nor my hell”

This person she’s been mentioning throughout the whole song is like a protector. This person allowed her to lose fear of her inner demons and her dreams.

You is what is birth taught
 Never leave it unresolved

Here she talks about certain traumas or issues that are learned as a child. Those problems that marked you in their childhood create the person that you are today. That is Biig Piig says that it should never be left unresolved.
Andando por el fuego
“Andando por el fuego” means going through the fire. She smiles as she goes through the fire, this could mean that she is still strong even when she’s facing life struggles.
Sigo sonriendo
I keep smiling
No se donde puedo
I don’t know where I can
No se donde ir
I don’t know where to go
